<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>How to Use This Document:</p>
<p>Hey there! This is TroyL, your friendly neighborhood guy. I’ve had a lot of people asking questions about author pages and ways to make them as low maintenance as possible, so I created this template. The coolest thing about this template? It will AUTOMATICALLY display everything you write on the site, so you’ll not have to worry about updating your lists ever again!</p>
<p>Take a look down there. See where it says “YOUR NAME HERE”? Just type your Wikidot User Name, exactly as it’s spelling, between those quotation marks, leaving no spaces. Bam. You’re done! Feel free to fill out the rest of the document however you want, screwing around with it however you please, but leave the modules as they are! There’s a chance, after the tag update, that this template will be further updated to include more stuff, so keep your eyes open.</p>
<p>As a note, if you don’t have a Joke SCP or a Foundation Tales up yet, just delete that portion of the document. If you write one later, just copy/paste that part back in!</p>
<p>Final Note: Make sure you Tag your profile with the “author” tag when you’re finished! That way, it won’t show up on its own lists. Thanks, and I hope you like the template!</p>
<p>Template:</p>
<div class="code">
